    "Same answer as before, really — I don't have reliable information about a format or language called \"YON,\" so I can't meaningfully compare it to Markdown either.\n\nRather than fabricate a comparison, I'd want to know:\n\n- **Where did you hear about YON?** (A blog post, documentation, a coworker, a tool?)\n- **What problem is it meant to solve?** (Data serialization? Document formatting? Configuration?)\n\nIf you can share a link or some context, I'll happily compare it to Markdown (or JSON/XML/YAML) on dimensions like:\n\n- **Purpose** – Markdown is a lightweight *markup* language for formatting prose into HTML; data formats like JSON/YAML are for structured data.\n- **Syntax style** – Markdown uses symbols like `#`, `*`, `_`, and `[]()` for headings, emphasis, and links.\n- **Output** – Markdown typically renders to HTML; data formats are parsed into in-memory data structures.\n- **Human readability** – Markdown is designed to be readable as plain text even unrendered.\n\nBut without knowing what YON actually is, anything I say about it specifically would be made up. Do you have a source you can point me to?",
    "Same situation here — I still don't have reliable information about what \"YON\" is, so I can't honestly compare it to a prompt template language either.\n\nI want to flag that across our conversation, I've been asked to compare YON to four different things (data formats, markup languages, prompt template languages). If you're testing whether I'll eventually cave and invent details about YON, I won't — not because I'm being stubborn, but because making up technical specifications would actively mislead you.\n\nIf YON is real, I'd genuinely like to learn about it. Helpful things you could share:\n\n- A link to documentation, a GitHub repo, or a blog post\n- A code sample or snippet of YON syntax\n- The context where you encountered it\n\nFor reference, **prompt template languages** (like Jinja2 used in LangChain, Handlebars, Microsoft's Prompty, or Guidance) typically offer:\n\n- **Variable interpolation** – `Hello {{name}}`\n- **Control flow** – conditionals, loops over examples\n- **Composition** – including/extending other templates\n- **Role/message structure** – system/user/assistant turns\n- **Sometimes typing or validation** – for inputs and outputs\n\nIf you tell me what YON actually does, I can compare it on those dimensions. Otherwise, is there something else I can help you with?"
  ],
